                                    <measure unit="leaf" quantity="64">i+62+ii</measure>
                                    <note>63 folia, according to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/9HRU9IZC"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Fiaccadori1997Ripristino"/><title level="a">Ripristino dell’omelia etiopica sull’arcangelo Afnin</title><title level="j">Miscellanea Marciana</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Gianfranco</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Fiaccadori</t:surname></author><date>1997</date><biblScope unit="volume">12</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">45–51</biblScope></bibl></note>
                                    <measure unit="leaf" type="blank"/>
                                    <locus target="#i #1r #32v #33r #33v #55v #56r #56v #ii"/>
                                    <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                                        <height>210</height>
                                        <width>150</width>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>European foliation in the upper right corner of the
                                    folia. The initial unfoliated parchment folium is assigned the
                                    number <locus target="#i">i</locus>. The last unfoliated
                                    parchment folium assigned the number <locus target="#ii">ii</locus>. </foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <note> According to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/9HRU9IZC"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Fiaccadori1997Ripristino"/><title level="a">Ripristino dell’omelia etiopica sull’arcangelo Afnin</title><title level="j">Miscellanea Marciana</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Gianfranco</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Fiaccadori</t:surname></author><date>1997</date><biblScope unit="volume">12</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">45–51</biblScope></bibl>,
                                        folios 1 to 63 are blindly ruled (<foreign xml:lang="it">rigatura a secco</foreign>). However, observations of
                                        the manuscript and its reproductions suggest that only
                                        folios 2 to 62 are ruled. This discrepancy might indicate
                                        that two folios—one at the beginning and one at the end—have
                                        been lost, or that Fiaccadori mistakenly counted unruled
                                        folios as ruled. Due to these uncertainties, the below
                                        reconstruction of the first and last quires may be imprecise
                                        and should therefore be considered with caution. Fiaccadori
                                        proposed a slightly different collation, excluding the first
                                        unnumbered folio (which may have been missing at the time)
                                        and considering folio 1 recto as part of the first quire,
                                        describing it as 1+8. He also described the last quire as
                                        consisting of folios 56 to 63, f. 63 being either lost or
                                        current ii. </note>
